  "body": "I'm trying to use clef as external signer and account manager. But, the problem is when I tried to set clef as geth signer, it keeps asking approval of list account even the rules already set like the example\r\n\r\n```js\r\nfunction ApproveListing(req) {\r\n    if (req.meta.scheme == \"ipc\"){ return \"Approve\"}\r\n}\r\n``` \r\n\r\nAs you see, list account is approved when the request is made from IPC and I connect geth to clef using this parameter\r\n\r\n```\r\n--signer=~/.clef/clef.ipc\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe this means requests made from geth automatically from IPC, right? But, why clef keeps asking for approval for that request? When I check the value of `req.meta.scheme`, the result is `NA`. Why is that?",
